\begin{gather*}
A-\lambda{I}=\begin{bmatrix}-7-\lambda&-9\\4&8-\lambda\end{bmatrix}.
\end{gather*}
\begin{align*}
p(\lambda)&=|A-\lambda{I}|=\begin{vmatrix}-7-\lambda&-9\\4&8-\lambda\end{vmatrix}.\\
&=(-7-\lambda)(8-\lambda)-(4\times-9)\\
&=-56-\lambda+\lambda^2+36\\
&=\lambda^2-\lambda-20\\
&=(\lambda-5)(\lambda+4)
\end{align*}
Solving $p(\lambda)=0$ yields the eigenvalues $\lambda_1=5$ and $\lambda_2=-4$.
Find the eigenvalues of \(\begin{bmatrix}-7&-9\\4&8\end{bmatrix}\).
$\lambda_1=5,\lambda_2=-4$
